                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>Secretary of State Acheson delivered a major foreign policy address on the
                    evening of November 29 which was broadcast from Washington to the National
                    Council of Churches of Christ in the United States meeting in Cleveland; for the
                    text, see Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, December 18,
                    1950, page 962. Regarding Korea, he termed Chinese Communist intervention a
                    premeditated act of brazen aggression, called on the Chinese Communist
                    authorities not to act as the dupes of others in opposing the United Nations,
                    and reiterated that the United States had no special interests in the area apart
                    from the interests of the majority of United Nations members in achieving
                    peace.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
